[1] Cholera - Iraq
Date: Wed 4 Nov 2008
Source: UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs
(OCHA), ReliefWeb, Government of Iraq & World Health Organization
(WHO) report [edited]
<http://reliefweb.int/rw/rwb.nsf/db900SID/PANA-7L4JT2?OpenDocument>


The recent report of Iraq Ministry of Health indicates that 738
laboratory-confirmed cholera cases have been detected and registered
in Iraq, up to 4 Nov 2008. Most of the new confirmed cases were from
Babil and Muthana. There have been 8 deaths (6 males and 2 females).
50 percent of the deaths have been in children below 5 years of age.

Epidemiological findings have indicated that contaminated water is
the most probable source of the outbreak. 737 cases have been
identified as Inaba and 1 case as Ogawa serotypes.

Province / No. districts / Date 1st case / Date most recent case /
Deaths / Cases
Diala / 1 / 9 Sep 2008 / 9 Sep 2008 / 0 / 1
Wasit / 1 / 30 Sep 2008 / 30 Sep 2008 / 0 / 2
Erbil / 2 / 14 Oct 2008 / 14 Oct 2008 / 0 / 2
Missan / 1 / 7 Sep 2008 / 28 Aug 2008 / 1 / 3
Anbar / 2 / 7 Sep 2008 / 1 Oct 2008 / 0 / 8
Muthana / 1 / 14 Oct 2008 / 1 Nov 2008 / 0 / 10
Najaf / 3 / 17 Sep 2008 / 28 Oct 2008 / 0 / 33
Kerbala / 3 / 5 Sep 2008 / 27 Oct 2008 / 0 / 55
Basra / 5 / 14 Sep 2008 / 6 Oct 2008 / 1 / 58
Baghdad / 12 / 18 Aug 2008 / 3 Nov 2008 / 1 / 92
Diwanyia / 4 / 20 Sep 2008 / 29 Oct 2008 / 2 / 207
Babil / 4 / 28 Aug 2008 / 2 Nov 2008 / 3 / 267
----------------------------------------------
Total: 39 / 7 Aug 2008 / 3 Nov 2008 / 8 / 738

