[5] Diarrhea, fatal - India (Assam)
Date: Sat 18 Oct 2008
Source: Merinews [edited]
<http://www.merinews.com/catFull.jsp?articleID=145078>


A total of 6 people have died and another 25 suffer from diarrhea in
the hospitals of Golaghat and Dergaon while allegation of inadequate
health facilities has come into focus. The people died between 12 to
17 Oct 2008. All those people belonged to Misamara Tea Estate of
Golaghat district.

It is to note that a total of 25-30 people died of diarrhea at the
same garden some 3 years back, too. People say that it is because of
impure water, which causes the disease among the tea-garden population.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Susan Baekeland

[Assam is in northeastern India and can be found on a map at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assam>. - Mod.LL]

